Narcose Public Good IPA (West Coast IPA)

OG: 1.060
FG: 1.014
ABV: 6,0%
IBU: 60

85% Viking Pilsner Malt
10% Viking Wheat Malt
5% Viking Munich Malt
5% Cane Sugar (Boil)

Mash in 63C
63C - 40’
72C - 15’
78C - 5’

Boil 60 minutes

Boil Ph: 5.1
20 IBU Magnum hops - 60’
Cane Sugar - 30’
10g/L Idaho 7 hops - Whirlpool

Yeast: American Ale - 0.75M cells/ml/Plato

Inoculate at 18 degrees Celsius

Ferment at 20 degrees Celsius

Release temperature to 22.5 degrees Celsius once fermentation reached 70%
attenuation

1st Dry Hop: 5g/L Mosaic hops at the end of fermentation (gravity ~ 1.018)

2nd Dry Hop: 5g/L El Dorado. 3 days after attenuation is reached, lower temperature
to 16 Celsius and add 2nd dry hop.

Water Profile:
Calcium: 75-125ppm
Chloride/Sulphate ratio: 1/3

Created by www.cervejarianarcose.com.br
